data.description: Have you been looking for a Home that can capture the beautiful images of nature and the city as the seasons change across the water and treetops? This Corner Unit at Edgewater Plaza Condos does just that. Located on the 29th floor, you'll have views of the East, South, and West, which include Lake Michigan, Foster Beach, DuSable LSD, and the City's landscape. Upon entry, you'll be greeted by a Foyer, which includes a large closet perfect when welcoming guests and for storage. The Foyer leads into the updated galley Kitchen that homes modern black granite countertops, custom quality maple KraftMaid cabinetry, mosaic tile backsplash, electric oven, fridge, dishwasher, microwave, and Breakfast Bar. Enjoy meals and Lake views in the Dining area which is also a passage to a Living Room that offers generous space for relaxing and entertaining. Circling back to the hallway, you'll pass another storage/coat closet before reaching the Bathroom, which has updated vanity and flooring, a shower/tub, and linen closet. Across the hall, before entering the Bedroom is a linen/broom closet. (This Unit does NOT lack storage space!) The Bedroom certainly delivers with adequate dimensions for any size bed, sunlight, and closet space, with organizers (shelves & drawers) that are nearly the length of the entire room. What's in the building? Amenities galore, with 24/7 Laundry Room on 2nd floor, dry cleaning and package room, a pool, deck, party rooms, fenced yard w/ grills, 24 hour door staff, garage parking, trash/recycling on every floor, storage, and a garden/outdoor space to be enjoyed by all Residents. Very pet friendly building. (NOTE: there may be additional fees for some amenities offered.) Monthly Assessments include nearly ALL utilities, only leaving you to have an electric account. What's in the neighborhood? Beaches, Trails along the Lake for biking/walking/jogging, Dining, Shopping, Public transportation, easy access to Downtown or the North Shore, and all the joys City living has to offer. (Easy access to Lake, trails, and beach at the rear of the building.) This property is being sold pursuant to Short-Sale. Subject to Lien Holder's Approval. Property is being sold AS-IS, WHERE IT STANDS. Information on MLS is assumed to be accurate, but NOT guaranteed. Buyer/Buyer's Agent should verify all relevant MLS information. Please allow approx. 45-60 days (+/-) for Closing to occur. NOTE: Taxes do NOT reflect ANY exemptions. ONLY OFFERS WITH CASH OR CONVENTIONAL LOANS WILL BE CONSIDERED. PROOF OF FUNDS FOR PURCHASE / DOWN PAYMENT WILL BE REQUIRED WITH ALL WRITTEN OFFERS. With just shy of 1000 sqft of living space, the building's amenities, the amazing views, and the awesome location, there is no doubt the value this opportunity presents. Schedule a viewing of your new place to call Home. (Video tours available, upon request.)
